  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pre-heat the grill to a high heat then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\"><span class=\"text-danger\">[390ml] </span>[600ml]<strong> </span>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked, then rinse the rice under <strong>cold running water </strong>until cool and set aside until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1726233357037-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1726233357037-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1726233357037-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1726233357037-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1726233357037-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> (you'll use the rest later!), 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Add the<strong> chicken strips </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1726233360925-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1726233360925-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1726233360925-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1726233360925-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1726233360925-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drizzle a baking tray with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (to prevent the chicken from sticking)</p><p>Add the <strong>coated chicken</strong> to the tray and put it under the grill for 10-12 min, turning the chicken half way through cooking, until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and starting to char – this is your <strong>tandoori chicken</strong></p>",
